<TITLE> President being treated for viral fever </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 24 (bdnews24.com) -- President Iajuddin Ahmed is recovering from a viral fever, after he was placed under intensive care at Dhaka Combined Military Hospital late Monday night suffering, officials said Tuesday. Md Sirajul Islam, secretary (public division) to the president, told bdnews24.com: "The president's condition is better now." "The president took breakfast in the morning. I spoke to him," he said. On how many days Iajuddin was expected to stay in the hospital, the secretary said: "The doctors have not told us anything specifically about that. Viral fever takes time to treat." President Iajuddin was admitted to Dhaka CMH shortly before 11pm Monday night, running a high temperature. Bangabhaban staffer Abdur Rahman said the president was accompanied to the hospital by his wife. bdne
